#!/usr/bin/env bash
# spark-set-model - Change the active model configuration
#
# Updates model.env with the new model (and optional overrides).
#
# Split mode:  syncs config to secondary node (dyad) and restarts
#              vllm-standalone on both nodes.  Includes a pre-flight
#              check that the model cache exists on the secondary
#              before committing to a restart.
#
# Ray/Swarm:   updates config only — run 'spark-stop && spark-serve'
#              to apply.
set -euo pipefail

SOURCE="${BASH_SOURCE[0]}"
while [ -L "$SOURCE" ]; do SOURCE="$(readlink "$SOURCE")"; done
SCRIPT_DIR="$(cd "$(dirname "$SOURCE")" && pwd)"
source "${SCRIPT_DIR}/../lib/spark-common.sh"

if [[ "${1:-}" == "--help" || "${1:-}" == "-h" ]]; then
    cat << 'EOF'
spark-set-model — change the active model configuration

Updates model.env with the new model name and optional parameter overrides.
Behavior differs significantly based on the current topology mode.

WHAT IT DOES
============
All modes:
  Writes MODEL_NAME (and any --tp/--ctx/--mem/--served overrides) to
  ~/.config/spark-tools/model.env using sed in-place substitution.
  Only values explicitly passed are changed; others are left as-is.

Split mode (monad + dyad each running an independent vLLM instance):
  ADDITIONALLY performs a 4-step live update sequence:
    [1/4] Pre-flight: SSH to dyad; check model's HuggingFace cache directory
          exists at: $HF_HOME/hub/models--<Org>--<Model>/
          If not found: warns, shows download command, prompts y/N to continue.
          If N: aborts (model.env is updated locally but NOT synced — nodes are
          out of sync until you run spark-set-model again).
    [2/4] Sync: scp model.env → dyad:~/.config/spark-tools/model.env
    [3/4] Restart: sudo systemctl restart vllm-standalone  (on monad)
    [4/4] Restart: ssh dyad sudo systemctl restart vllm-standalone
          Waits 5s then prints the first 12 lines of systemctl status from both
          nodes so you can see whether the service came up cleanly.

Ray / Swarm mode:
  Config-only update. Services are NOT restarted automatically.
  Run 'spark-stop && spark-serve' to apply.

WHY THE DIFFERENCE
==================
In split mode, both nodes serve independently and restart is safe immediately —
each node's vllm-standalone is self-contained. Keeping both nodes in sync is
critical: an unsync'd dyad will serve the old model while monad serves the new.

In ray/cluster mode, the model is sharded across both nodes simultaneously.
Restarting requires a coordinated sequence: stop spark-ray-vllm, stop
spark-ray-worker, stop spark-ray-head, then restart in reverse order.
That sequence is handled by 'spark-stop && spark-serve', not here.

PRECONDITIONS
=============
  - spark-init must have been run; model.env must exist
    (error if missing: "Run 'spark-init' to create it.")
  - The model must already be downloaded on monad
  - For split mode additionally:
      - Passwordless SSH from monad to dyad as current $USER
      - Model weights downloaded on dyad at:
          $HF_HOME/hub/models--<Org>--<Model>/
          where "Org/Model" → "models--Org--Model" (slashes become --)
      - sudo access on both nodes (to restart systemd services)

USAGE
=====
  spark-set-model <model-name> [OPTIONS]

ARGUMENTS
=========
  model-name    HuggingFace repository ID. Required.
                Format: Org/ModelName
                Example: nvidia/Qwen3-235B-A22B-FP4

OPTIONS
=======
  --tp SIZE           Tensor parallel size. Number of GPUs used for this model.
                      Split mode: use 1 (each node serves independently, TP=1).
                      Cluster mode: use 2 (TP=2 sharded across monad + dyad).
                      WARNING: if current model.env has TP_SIZE=2 and the current
                      topology is split, you will see a warning but are not blocked.
                      Use --tp 1 explicitly when switching to split.
                      Default: keep current value in model.env.

  --ctx LENGTH        Max context length in tokens.
                      Per-node overrides in node.env.monad / node.env.dyad can
                      set different context windows per node (e.g. monad=131072,
                      dyad=262144 when dyad has more GPU headroom).
                      Default: keep current value in model.env.

  --mem UTIL          GPU memory utilization fraction, 0.0–1.0.
                      Per-node overrides in node.env.monad / node.env.dyad can
                      set different utilization per node.
                      Default: keep current value in model.env.

  --served NAME       Model alias returned by the /v1/models API endpoint.
                      Clients use this short name instead of the full HF path.
                      Example: --served qwen3 so clients call model="qwen3".
                      Default: keep current value (empty = use full MODEL_NAME).

  --skip-preflight    Skip the model cache directory check on dyad.
                      Use when you know the cache exists but the directory probe
                      might fail (custom HF_HOME, symlinked cache, NFS mount).
                      Split mode only — has no effect in ray/swarm mode.

SIDE EFFECTS
============
  - Modifies ~/.config/spark-tools/model.env in-place (sed substitution)
  - Split mode: also writes to dyad:~/.config/spark-tools/model.env via scp
  - Split mode: immediately restarts vllm-standalone on both nodes
  - Split mode abort (user enters N at prompt): model.env updated locally but
    NOT synced to dyad. Nodes are out of sync.
    Recover with: spark-set-model <previous-model>

EXAMPLES
========
Switch model (split mode — shows the full 4-step sequence):
  $ spark-set-model nvidia/Qwen3-235B-A22B-FP4
  Model updated in /home/user/.config/spark-tools/model.env:
    MODEL_NAME=nvidia/Qwen3-235B-A22B-FP4

  === Split mode: syncing and restarting both nodes ===

  ==> [1/4] Pre-flight: checking model cache on dyad...
    ✓ Cache found on dyad:
      /home/user/.cache/huggingface/hub/models--nvidia--Qwen3-235B-A22B-FP4
      42 .safetensors file(s) in snapshot

  ==> [2/4] Syncing model.env → dyad...
    ✓ Synced: /home/user/.config/spark-tools/model.env → dyad:...model.env

  ==> [3/4] Restarting vllm-standalone on monad...
    ✓ vllm-standalone restarted on monad

  ==> [4/4] Restarting vllm-standalone on dyad...
    ✓ vllm-standalone restarted on dyad

  Waiting for vLLM instances to start (large models take several minutes)...

  --- monad: vllm-standalone ---
    ... systemctl status output (12 lines) ...

  --- dyad: vllm-standalone ---
    ... systemctl status output (12 lines) ...

  Monitor logs:
    journalctl -u vllm-standalone -f                      # monad
    ssh dyad journalctl -u vllm-standalone -f             # dyad

  Check health once ready:
    spark-check

Switch model with explicit TP and context (ray/swarm mode — config only):
  $ spark-set-model Qwen/Qwen3-Coder-480B-A22B-FP4 --tp 2 --ctx 131072
  Model updated in /home/user/.config/spark-tools/model.env:
    MODEL_NAME=Qwen/Qwen3-Coder-480B-A22B-FP4
    TP_SIZE=2
    MAX_MODEL_LEN=131072

  Restart to apply: spark-stop && spark-serve

Set a short client-facing model name:
  $ spark-set-model meta-llama/Llama-3.3-70B-Instruct --served llama3
  Model updated in /home/user/.config/spark-tools/model.env:
    MODEL_NAME=meta-llama/Llama-3.3-70B-Instruct
    SERVED_MODEL_NAME=llama3

  Restart to apply: spark-stop && spark-serve

Pre-flight failure — model not downloaded on dyad (split mode):
  $ spark-set-model SomeOrg/NewModel
  Model updated in /home/user/.config/spark-tools/model.env:
    MODEL_NAME=SomeOrg/NewModel

  === Split mode: syncing and restarting both nodes ===

  ==> [1/4] Pre-flight: checking model cache on dyad...

  WARNING: Model cache not found on dyad.
  Expected: /home/user/.cache/huggingface/hub/models--SomeOrg--NewModel

  The model must be downloaded on dyad before vllm-standalone can serve it.

  To pre-download on dyad:
    ssh dyad huggingface-cli download 'SomeOrg/NewModel'

  Continue anyway? [y/N] N

  Aborted. Config was updated locally but NOT synced.
  Restore previous model with: spark-set-model <old-model>

EXIT CODES
==========
  0   Success (config updated; in split mode, services restarted on both nodes)
  1   model.env not found, SSH failure, bad argument, or user entered N at prompt

SEE ALSO
========
  spark-help          Full list of spark commands with descriptions
  spark-init          Initialize configuration (creates model.env)
  spark-mode          View/change topology (split/cluster) and orchestration
  spark-serve         Start inference services (ray/swarm mode after config change)
  spark-stop          Stop inference services
  spark-check         Verify the API endpoint is responding correctly
EOF
    exit 0
fi

spark_load_config

[[ $# -lt 1 ]] && spark_die "Model name required. Use --help for usage."

NEW_MODEL="$1"
shift

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Parse optional overrides
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NEW_TP=""
NEW_CTX=""
NEW_MEM=""
NEW_SERVED=""
SET_SERVED=false
SKIP_PREFLIGHT=false

while [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do
    case "$1" in
        --tp)              shift; NEW_TP="${1:-}";     [[ -z "$NEW_TP" ]]  && spark_die "--tp requires a value" ;;
        --ctx)             shift; NEW_CTX="${1:-}";    [[ -z "$NEW_CTX" ]] && spark_die "--ctx requires a value" ;;
        --mem)             shift; NEW_MEM="${1:-}";    [[ -z "$NEW_MEM" ]] && spark_die "--mem requires a value" ;;
        --served)          shift; NEW_SERVED="${1:-}"; SET_SERVED=true ;;
        --skip-preflight)  SKIP_PREFLIGHT=true ;;
        *) spark_die "Unknown option: $1. Use --help for usage." ;;
    esac
    shift
done

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Apply split-mode TP default (1 per node, not 2)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
if [[ "$SPARK_MODE" == "split" && -z "$NEW_TP" ]]; then
    CURRENT_TP="${TP_SIZE:-}"
    # Only suggest TP=1 if current config has TP=2 (likely a leftover from ray mode)
    if [[ "${CURRENT_TP}" == "2" ]]; then
        _yellow "WARNING: Current TP_SIZE=2 — split mode runs one vLLM per node."
        _yellow "         TP=2 requires two GPUs on a single node. Did you mean --tp 1?"
        echo ""
    fi
fi

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Update model.env (local)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
if [[ ! -f "$SPARK_MODEL_ENV" ]]; then
    spark_die "model.env not found: ${SPARK_MODEL_ENV}
Run 'spark-init' to create it."
fi

sed -i "s|^MODEL_NAME=.*|MODEL_NAME=${NEW_MODEL}|" "$SPARK_MODEL_ENV"
[[ -n "$NEW_TP" ]]          && sed -i "s/^TP_SIZE=.*/TP_SIZE=${NEW_TP}/"                      "$SPARK_MODEL_ENV"
[[ -n "$NEW_CTX" ]]         && sed -i "s/^MAX_MODEL_LEN=.*/MAX_MODEL_LEN=${NEW_CTX}/"        "$SPARK_MODEL_ENV"
[[ -n "$NEW_MEM" ]]         && sed -i "s/^GPU_MEM_UTIL=.*/GPU_MEM_UTIL=${NEW_MEM}/"          "$SPARK_MODEL_ENV"
[[ "$SET_SERVED" == true ]] && sed -i "s/^SERVED_MODEL_NAME=.*/SERVED_MODEL_NAME=${NEW_SERVED}/" "$SPARK_MODEL_ENV"

echo "Model updated in ${SPARK_MODEL_ENV}:"
echo "  MODEL_NAME=${NEW_MODEL}"
[[ -n "$NEW_TP" ]]          && echo "  TP_SIZE=${NEW_TP}"
[[ -n "$NEW_CTX" ]]         && echo "  MAX_MODEL_LEN=${NEW_CTX}"
[[ -n "$NEW_MEM" ]]         && echo "  GPU_MEM_UTIL=${NEW_MEM}"
[[ "$SET_SERVED" == true ]] && echo "  SERVED_MODEL_NAME=${NEW_SERVED}"
echo ""

# ===========================================================================
# SPLIT MODE: sync → dyad, restart both nodes
# ===========================================================================
if [[ "$SPARK_MODE" == "split" ]]; then

    PRIMARY="${SPARK_PRIMARY_HOST}"
    SECONDARY="${SPARK_SECONDARY_HOST}"

    echo "=== Split mode: syncing and restarting both nodes ==="
    echo ""

    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Step 1/4 — Pre-flight: check model cache on secondary
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    echo "==> [1/4] Pre-flight: checking model cache on ${SECONDARY}..."

    # Convert HuggingFace repo ID to HF hub cache directory name.
    # e.g.  "Qwen/Qwen3-Coder-Next-FP8" → "models--Qwen--Qwen3-Coder-Next-FP8"
    MODEL_CACHE_DIR="models--$(echo "$NEW_MODEL" | tr '/' '--')"
    REMOTE_HF_HUB="${HF_HOME:-$HOME/.cache/huggingface}/hub"

    CACHE_FOUND=false
    if [[ "$SKIP_PREFLIGHT" == true ]]; then
        echo "  (pre-flight skipped via --skip-preflight)"
        CACHE_FOUND=true
    elif spark_ssh "$SECONDARY" \
            "test -d '${REMOTE_HF_HUB}/${MODEL_CACHE_DIR}'" 2>/dev/null; then
        echo "  ✓ Cache found on ${SECONDARY}:"
        echo "    ${REMOTE_HF_HUB}/${MODEL_CACHE_DIR}"

        # Count snapshot files as a basic completeness signal
        SNAP_COUNT=$(spark_ssh "$SECONDARY" \
            "find '${REMOTE_HF_HUB}/${MODEL_CACHE_DIR}/snapshots' \
             -maxdepth 2 -name '*.safetensors' 2>/dev/null | wc -l" 2>/dev/null \
            || echo "?")
        echo "    ${SNAP_COUNT} .safetensors file(s) in snapshot"
        CACHE_FOUND=true
    else
        echo ""
        _yellow "  WARNING: Model cache not found on ${SECONDARY}."
        _yellow "  Expected: ${REMOTE_HF_HUB}/${MODEL_CACHE_DIR}"
        _yellow ""
        _yellow "  The model must be downloaded on ${SECONDARY} before vllm-standalone"
        _yellow "  can serve it. Without the cache, the service will fail to start."
        echo ""
        echo "  To pre-download on ${SECONDARY}:"
        echo "    ssh ${SECONDARY} huggingface-cli download '${NEW_MODEL}'"
        echo ""
        read -r -p "  Continue anyway? [y/N] " REPLY
        echo ""
        if [[ ! "${REPLY,,}" =~ ^y ]]; then
            echo "Aborted. Config was updated locally but NOT synced."
            echo "Restore previous model with: spark-set-model <old-model>"
            exit 1
        fi
    fi
    echo ""

    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Step 2/4 — Sync model.env → secondary
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    echo "==> [2/4] Syncing model.env → ${SECONDARY}..."

    # Ensure remote config directory exists
    REMOTE_CONFIG_DIR="${SPARK_CONFIG_DIR}"
    spark_ssh "$SECONDARY" "mkdir -p '${REMOTE_CONFIG_DIR}'" 2>/dev/null

    scp -o ConnectTimeout=5 -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no \
        "$SPARK_MODEL_ENV" \
        "${SECONDARY}:${SPARK_MODEL_ENV}"

    echo "  ✓ Synced: ${SPARK_MODEL_ENV} → ${SECONDARY}:${SPARK_MODEL_ENV}"
    echo ""

    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Step 3/4 — Restart vllm-standalone on primary (this node)
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    echo "==> [3/4] Restarting vllm-standalone on ${PRIMARY}..."

    if sudo systemctl restart vllm-standalone 2>/dev/null; then
        echo "  ✓ vllm-standalone restarted on ${PRIMARY}"
    else
        _yellow "  WARNING: Could not restart vllm-standalone on ${PRIMARY}"
        _yellow "           sudo may be required.  Restart manually:"
        _yellow "           sudo systemctl restart vllm-standalone"
    fi
    echo ""

    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Step 4/4 — Restart vllm-standalone on secondary
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    echo "==> [4/4] Restarting vllm-standalone on ${SECONDARY}..."

    if spark_ssh "$SECONDARY" "sudo systemctl restart vllm-standalone" 2>/dev/null; then
        echo "  ✓ vllm-standalone restarted on ${SECONDARY}"
    else
        _yellow "  WARNING: Could not restart vllm-standalone on ${SECONDARY}"
        _yellow "           Restart manually:"
        _yellow "           ssh ${SECONDARY} sudo systemctl restart vllm-standalone"
    fi
    echo ""

    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Wait and show brief status
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    echo "Waiting for vLLM instances to start (large models take several minutes)..."
    sleep 5
    echo ""

    echo "--- ${PRIMARY}: vllm-standalone ---"
    sudo systemctl --no-pager status vllm-standalone 2>/dev/null \
        | head -12 \
        | sed 's/^/  /' \
        || true
    echo ""

    echo "--- ${SECONDARY}: vllm-standalone ---"
    spark_ssh "$SECONDARY" \
        "sudo systemctl --no-pager status vllm-standalone 2>/dev/null | head -12" \
        2>/dev/null \
        | sed 's/^/  /' \
        || true
    echo ""

    echo "Monitor logs:"
    echo "  journalctl -u vllm-standalone -f                      # ${PRIMARY}"
    echo "  ssh ${SECONDARY} journalctl -u vllm-standalone -f     # ${SECONDARY}"
    echo ""
    echo "Check health once ready:"
    echo "  spark-check"

# ===========================================================================
# RAY / SWARM MODE: config-only update
# ===========================================================================
else
    echo "Restart to apply: spark-stop && spark-serve"
fi
